COMMS: FLASH TRAFFIC — COMNAVAIRLANT TO PATROL GROUP DELTA.
COMMS: Soviet surface group confirmed transiting Norwegian Sea. One Kirov-class battlecruiser, two Udaloy escorts. Heading two-one-zero. Speed eighteen.
INTEL: SIGINT indicates the formation departed Severomorsk forty-eight hours ago. Destination unknown. Assessment is a surge deployment — not an exercise.
COMMS: Your orders: shadow the formation. Maintain continuous sensor contact for forty-five minutes. Do not close inside thirty nautical miles.
INTEL: One of the Udaloys broke formation twenty minutes ago. It is sprinting toward your last reported position at twenty-five knots.
INTEL: They are not lost. They know exactly where you are.
COMMS: Weapons free only if fired upon. Your mission is intelligence — not engagement. Keep eyes on the Kirov.
COMMS: COMMS out.
